Package: restoptr
Type: Package
Title: 'restoptr' Ecological Restoration Planning
Version: 0.0.0.99999
Description:
    `restoptr` is a flexible ecological restoration planning framework. In 
    `restoptr`, a restoration planning problem starts from an existing habitat
    (typically a binary raster), where the aim is to identify optimal areas that
    are suitable for restoration. Several constraints are available to define
    what is expected for a suitable area for (e.g. it must be connected, compact,
    must respect a budget, etc). Several optimization objective are also available
    to define what is a good restoration area (e.g. it must reduce fragmentation,
    increase ecological connectivity, minimize costs, etc.).
